WEBVTT

00:18.101 --> 00:20.060
[CHITTERlNG]

00:28.445 --> 00:30.446
[VOICES WHISPERING lNDISTINCTLY]

00:37.120 --> 00:41.081
SCRlMGEOUR:
These are dark times, there is no denying.

00:41.666 --> 00:47.296
Our world has, perhaps,
faced no greater threat than it does today.

00:48.298 --> 00:52.259
But l say this to our citizenry:

00:52.427 --> 00:56.305
We, ever your servants...

00:56.473 --> 00:59.141
...will continue to defend your liberty...

00:59.309 --> 01:03.645
...and repel the forces
that seek to take it from you.

01:04.856 --> 01:10.152
Your Ministry remains...

01:10.653 --> 01:12.654
...strong.

01:15.825 --> 01:17.826
[THUNDER RUMBLlNG]

01:17.994 --> 01:19.995
[RAlNDROPS PATTERING]

01:30.006 --> 01:32.174
MRS. GRANGER:
Hermione. Tea's ready, darling.

01:32.342 --> 01:34.301
Coming, Mom.

01:38.223 --> 01:40.140
VERNON:
Come on, Dudley, hurry up.

01:40.308 --> 01:43.352
DUDLEY: l still don't understand
why we have to leave.

01:43.520 --> 01:48.273
VERNON: Because, unh,
it's not safe for us here anymore.

02:03.665 --> 02:08.043
Ron, tell your father
supper's nearly ready.

02:13.049 --> 02:14.758
MR. GRANGER:
Is this in Australia?

02:14.926 --> 02:16.885
MRS. GRANGER:
Looks wonderful, doesn't it?

02:17.053 --> 02:21.932
MAN [ON TV]: Three and a half thousand
kilometers along Australia's east coast.

02:23.226 --> 02:24.768
Obliviate.

04:31.896 --> 04:33.897
[CHATTERlNG]

04:39.112 --> 04:40.779
VOLDEMORT:
Severus.

04:40.947 --> 04:44.324
I was beginning to worry
you had lost your way.

04:44.492 --> 04:47.953
Come, we've saved you a seat.

04:52.375 --> 04:53.709
You bring news, l trust?

04:53.876 --> 04:57.546
It will happen Saturday next, at nighftall.

04:57.714 --> 05:00.090
YAXLEY:
I've heard differently, my Lord.

05:00.258 --> 05:03.385
Dawlish, the Auror,
has let slip that the Potter boy...

05:03.553 --> 05:06.680
...will not be moved
until the 30th of this month.

05:07.098 --> 05:08.390
The day before he turns 1 7.

05:08.558 --> 05:11.768
This is a false trail.

05:12.437 --> 05:16.606
The Auror Office no longer plays any part
in the protection of Harry Potter.

05:16.774 --> 05:21.153
Those closest to him believe
we have infiltrated the Ministry.

05:21.738 --> 05:23.363
Well, they got that right, haven't they?

05:23.531 --> 05:25.532
[ALL LAUGH]

05:27.827 --> 05:30.287
What say you, Pius?

05:33.833 --> 05:36.418
One hears many things, my Lord.

05:36.586 --> 05:39.171
Whether the truth is among them
is not clear.

05:39.338 --> 05:42.716
Heh. Spoken like a true politician.

05:42.884 --> 05:45.927
You will, I think,
prove most useful, Pius.

05:49.557 --> 05:52.768
-Where will he be taken, the boy?
SNAPE: To a safe house.

05:53.186 --> 05:55.812
Most likely the home of someone
in the Order.

05:55.980 --> 05:59.232
I'm told it's been given
every manner of protection possible.

05:59.400 --> 06:02.986
Once there,
it will be impractical to attack him.

06:03.571 --> 06:08.116
Ahem. My Lord.
I'd like to volunteer myself for this task.

06:08.284 --> 06:09.284
I want to kill the boy.

06:09.452 --> 06:10.452
[YELL lN DlSTANCE]

06:10.620 --> 06:11.828
Wormtail!

06:11.996 --> 06:14.915
Have l not spoken to you
about keeping our guest quiet?

06:15.166 --> 06:17.042
Yes, my Lord.

06:17.210 --> 06:19.878
Right away, my Lord.

06:20.129 --> 06:24.633
VOLDEMORT: As inspiring
as l find your bloodlust, Bellatrix...

06:25.051 --> 06:28.345
...l must be the one to kill Harry Potter.

06:30.807 --> 06:35.644
But l face an unfortunate complication.

06:35.812 --> 06:40.982
That my wand and Potter's
share the same core.

06:42.235 --> 06:48.824
They are, in some ways, twins.

06:48.991 --> 06:53.662
We can wound,
but not fatally harm one another.

06:55.289 --> 06:58.083
If l am to kill him...

06:58.751 --> 07:02.504
...l must do it with another's wand.

07:04.507 --> 07:10.220
Come, surely one of you
would like the honor?

07:11.848 --> 07:13.515
Mm?

07:15.184 --> 07:20.021
What about you, Lucius?

07:22.525 --> 07:23.900
My Lord?

07:24.068 --> 07:26.027
"My Lord?"

07:27.113 --> 07:30.740
I require your wand.

07:44.046 --> 07:46.548
Do I detect elm?

07:46.716 --> 07:48.675
Yes, my Lord.

07:54.599 --> 07:57.559
And the core?

07:57.727 --> 07:59.895
Dragon. Ahem.

08:00.062 --> 08:01.730
Dragon heartstring, my Lord.

08:01.898 --> 08:04.065
-Dragon heartstring.
-Mm.

08:19.790 --> 08:21.583
VOLDEMORT:
To those of you who do not know...

08:21.751 --> 08:24.419
...we are joined tonight
by Miss Charity Burbage...

08:24.587 --> 08:30.091
...who, until recently, taught at Hogwarts
School of Witchcraft and Wizardry.

08:30.259 --> 08:33.720
Her specialty was Muggle Studies.

08:33.888 --> 08:35.889
[ALL CHUCKLE]

08:36.933 --> 08:43.188
It is Miss Burbage's belief
that Muggles are not so different from us.

08:43.356 --> 08:46.983
She would, given her way...

08:47.777 --> 08:49.694
...have us mate with them.

08:49.862 --> 08:51.863
[ALL CHUCKLE]

08:53.366 --> 08:59.579
To her, the mixture of magical
and Muggle blood is not an abomination...

08:59.747 --> 09:02.791
...but something to be encouraged.

09:03.834 --> 09:05.710
BURBAGE:
Severus.

09:05.878 --> 09:07.837
Severus, please.

09:09.507 --> 09:11.675
We're friends.

09:16.472 --> 09:18.014
VOLDEMORT:
Avada Kedavra!

09:28.275 --> 09:30.318
Nagini.

09:33.906 --> 09:35.573
Dinner.

09:44.250 --> 09:45.417
[HlSSES]

10:10.860 --> 10:13.361
[HEDWIG SCREECHES]

11:13.756 --> 11:15.757
[ENGINE WHlRRlNG THEN STOPS]

11:20.888 --> 11:24.265
HAGRID: Hello, Harry.
HARRY: All right. Wow.

11:24.433 --> 11:25.558
Hello.

11:25.726 --> 11:28.603
HAGRID: You're looking fit.
-Yeah, he's absolutely gorgeous.

11:28.771 --> 11:31.272
What say we get undercover
before someone murders him?

11:31.440 --> 11:32.440
HARRY:
Evening.

11:34.110 --> 11:35.777
[GRUNTS]

11:37.321 --> 11:38.947
HARRY:
I thought you were looking after...

11:39.115 --> 11:40.949
-...the Prime Minister.
-You are more important.

11:41.992 --> 11:45.078
-Hello, Harry. Bill Weasley.
-Oh. Pleasure to meet you.

11:45.246 --> 11:48.248
FRED: He was never always this handsome.
-Dead ugly.

11:48.415 --> 11:49.791
True enough.

11:49.959 --> 11:52.502
Owe it all to a werewolf,
name of Greyback.

11:52.670 --> 11:56.047
-Hope to repay the favor one day.
-You're still beautiful to me, William.

11:56.423 --> 12:00.051
LUPlN: Just remember, Fleur,
Bill takes his steaks on the raw side now.

12:00.219 --> 12:02.554
My husband, the joker.

12:02.721 --> 12:05.974
By the way, wait till you hear the news.
Remus and l--

12:06.142 --> 12:08.601
All right. We'll have time
for a cozy catch-up later.

12:08.769 --> 12:11.729
We've got to get the hell out of here.
And soon.

12:12.398 --> 12:15.650
Potter, you're underage, which means
you've still got the Trace on you.

12:15.818 --> 12:16.860
What's the Trace?

12:17.027 --> 12:19.696
If you sneeze, the Ministry will know
who wipes your nose.

12:19.864 --> 12:23.032
We have to use those means of transport
the Trace can't detect:

12:23.200 --> 12:25.535
Brooms, Thestrals and the like.
We go in pairs.

12:25.703 --> 12:29.497
That way, if anyone's out there waiting
for us, and I reckon there will be...

12:29.665 --> 12:32.167
...they won't know which Harry Potter
is the real one.

12:32.585 --> 12:33.751
The real one?

12:35.087 --> 12:38.173
I believe you're familiar
with this particular brew.

12:38.340 --> 12:40.675
No. Absolutely not.

12:40.843 --> 12:42.177
I told you he'd take it well.

12:42.344 --> 12:45.471
No, if you think l'm gonna let everyone
risk their lives for me, l--

12:45.639 --> 12:48.683
-Never done that before, have we?
-No. No. This is different.

12:48.851 --> 12:50.852
I mean, taking that, becoming me. No.

12:51.020 --> 12:52.854
Well, none of us really fancy it, mate.

12:53.022 --> 12:57.192
Imagine if something went wrong, and
we ended up a scrawny, specky git forever.

12:57.359 --> 12:59.027
MOODY:
Everyone here is of age, Potter.

12:59.737 --> 13:01.196
They've all agreed to take the risk.

13:01.363 --> 13:02.363
[MUNDUNGUS CLEARS THROAT]

13:02.531 --> 13:05.450
Technically, l've been coerced.

13:05.618 --> 13:07.827
Mundungus Fletcher, Mr. Potter.

13:07.995 --> 13:10.538
-Always been a huge admirer.
-Nip it, Mundungus.

13:11.874 --> 13:14.375
All right, Granger, as discussed.

13:14.543 --> 13:17.253
-Blimey, Hermione.
MOODY: Straight in here, if you please.

13:27.139 --> 13:31.309
For those of you who haven't taken
Polyjuice Potion before, fair warning:

13:31.477 --> 13:33.102
It tastes like goblin piss.

13:33.270 --> 13:36.231
Have a lot of experiences with that,
do you, Mad-Eye?

13:37.149 --> 13:40.068
Just trying to diffuse the tension.

13:41.111 --> 13:42.904
Oh.

13:45.991 --> 13:47.742
Ugh.

13:48.077 --> 13:51.371
[ALL GRUNTING]

14:12.017 --> 14:14.102
BOTH:
Wow, we're identical.

14:14.270 --> 14:15.270
MOODY:
Not yet, you're not.

14:18.983 --> 14:21.567
GEORGE: Haven't got anything
a bit more sporting, have you?

14:21.735 --> 14:23.194
FRED:
I don't really fancy this color.

14:23.362 --> 14:26.155
MOODY: Well, fancy this, you're not you.
So shut it and strip.

14:26.323 --> 14:27.907
MUNDUNGUS:
All right, all right.

14:28.075 --> 14:29.617
You'll need to change too, Potter.

14:30.119 --> 14:32.787
FLEUR:
Bill, look away. I'm hideous.

14:32.955 --> 14:35.248
RON:
I knew she was lying about that tattoo.

14:35.416 --> 14:37.834
HERMlONE:
Harry, your eyesight really is awful.

14:38.002 --> 14:41.713
Right, then. We'll be pairing off.
Each Potter will have a protector.

14:41.880 --> 14:45.174
Mundungus, stick tight to me.
I wanna keep an eye on you.

14:45.718 --> 14:47.552
-As for Harry--
ALL: Yes?

14:48.387 --> 14:49.804
The real Harry.

14:49.972 --> 14:52.307
-Where the devil are you, anyway?
-Here.

14:52.474 --> 14:54.475
MOODY:
You'll ride with Hagrid.

14:54.643 --> 14:59.647
I brought you here 1 6 years ago when
you were no bigger than a Bowtruckle.

14:59.815 --> 15:01.607
Seems only right that I should be...

15:01.859 --> 15:05.820
-...the one to take you away now.
-Yes, it's all very touching. Let's go.

15:08.073 --> 15:10.074
[HEDWIG SCREECHlNG]

15:19.209 --> 15:23.046
MOODY: Head for the Burrows.
We'll rendezvous there.

15:23.589 --> 15:25.673
On the count of three.

15:25.841 --> 15:27.550
Hold tight, Harry.

15:27.718 --> 15:29.510
MOODY:
One...

15:30.387 --> 15:32.180
...two...

15:38.604 --> 15:40.396
...three!

16:10.385 --> 16:13.554
DEATH EATER 1 : Which one?
DEATH EATER 2: Where are you?

16:14.765 --> 16:16.516
He's on your right!

16:16.683 --> 16:18.309
He's over there!

16:18.477 --> 16:20.144
DEATH EATER 3:
Down!

16:25.609 --> 16:27.276
Hagrid, we have to help the others!

16:27.694 --> 16:30.571
I can't do that, Harry. Mad-Eye's orders.

16:37.538 --> 16:39.330
Hang on.

16:43.127 --> 16:45.211
Stupefy!

16:52.427 --> 16:53.845
[HORN HONKS]

16:54.096 --> 16:55.429
[GASPS]

16:58.934 --> 17:00.017
Hang on, Harry.

17:01.728 --> 17:03.271
[GRUNTS]

17:09.945 --> 17:11.779
Hagrid.

17:24.126 --> 17:25.293
[SCREECHING]
[GRUNTS]

17:29.006 --> 17:31.299
HARRY:
No. No.

17:42.895 --> 17:45.479
[GROANING]

17:53.363 --> 17:55.364
VOLDEMORT:
Harry.

18:21.850 --> 18:23.684
[YELLING]

18:45.624 --> 18:48.000
[RUMBLING]

18:57.678 --> 18:59.095
[GRUNTS]

19:15.320 --> 19:18.406
MOLLY:
Harry. Hagrid.

19:19.783 --> 19:23.244
What happened? Where are the others?

19:23.412 --> 19:24.578
Is no one else back?

19:24.746 --> 19:28.332
HAGRID: They were on us right from
the start, Molly. We didn't stand a chance.

19:28.500 --> 19:31.669
Well, thank goodness
you two are all right.

19:31.837 --> 19:34.422
HAGRID: The Death Eaters were
waiting for us. lt was an ambush.

19:34.589 --> 19:36.966
GINNY: Ron and Tonks
should've already been back.

19:37.134 --> 19:38.342
Dad and Fred as well.

19:41.263 --> 19:42.930
LUPlN:
Here!

19:43.598 --> 19:47.018
Quick. lnto the house.

19:50.689 --> 19:52.773
Oh, my boy.

19:54.943 --> 19:57.445
Oh. Oh.

19:57.821 --> 19:58.863
[BOTH GRUNT]

19:59.031 --> 20:00.323
-Lupin!
GINNY: What are you doing?

20:02.868 --> 20:05.786
What creature sat in the corner...

20:05.954 --> 20:09.290
...the first time Harry Potter
visited my office in Hogwarts?

20:09.458 --> 20:11.083
-Are you mad?
-What creature?!

20:11.251 --> 20:13.085
A Grindylow.

20:16.548 --> 20:18.799
[HARRY SIGHS]

20:19.426 --> 20:21.093
LUPlN:
We've been betrayed.

20:21.261 --> 20:23.637
Voldemort knew
you were being moved tonight.

20:23.805 --> 20:26.724
I had to make sure
you weren't an impostor.

20:29.394 --> 20:30.853
[WHOOSH lN DlSTANCE]

20:33.857 --> 20:35.316
Wait.

20:38.320 --> 20:42.823
The last words Albus Dumbledore spoke
to the pair of us?

20:44.659 --> 20:48.996
"Harry is the best hope we have.
Trust him."

20:53.543 --> 20:54.668
What gave you away?

20:54.836 --> 20:57.963
Hedwig, I think.
She was trying to protect me.

21:14.564 --> 21:15.731
Thanks.

21:15.899 --> 21:18.067
TONKS:
Deserves that. Brilliant, he was.

21:18.235 --> 21:21.362
-l wouldn't be standing here without him.
HERMlONE: Really?

21:22.364 --> 21:25.032
Always the tone of surprise.

21:33.208 --> 21:34.417
We the last back?

21:35.710 --> 21:36.752
FRED:
Where's George?

21:58.066 --> 22:00.276
How you feeling, Georgie?

22:02.279 --> 22:03.821
Saint-like.

22:05.031 --> 22:06.240
Come again?

22:07.200 --> 22:10.744
Saint-like. l'm holy.

22:11.246 --> 22:14.331
I'm holey, Fred. Get it?

22:16.126 --> 22:20.838
The whole wide world of ear-related humor
and you go for "l'm holey."

22:21.006 --> 22:22.173
That's pathetic.

22:22.757 --> 22:25.092
Reckon l'm still better-looking than you.

22:28.597 --> 22:30.806
Mad-Eye's dead.

22:41.193 --> 22:44.945
Mundungus took one look at Voldemort
and Disapparated.

23:07.844 --> 23:09.887
MOODY:
Head for the Burrows.

23:10.680 --> 23:12.056
DUMBLEDORE:
This is beyond anything I imagined.

23:12.224 --> 23:14.850
SLUGHORN: Seven?
RIDDLE: Seven... ? A Horcrux.

23:15.018 --> 23:16.477
HARRY:
They could be hidden anywhere.

23:16.645 --> 23:18.812
SLUGHORN:
To rip the soul into seven pieces....

23:18.980 --> 23:21.982
HARRY: If you did destroy each Horcrux....
DUMBLEDORE: One destroys Voldemort.

23:25.570 --> 23:27.196
Trust me.

23:28.156 --> 23:31.700
VOLDEMORT:
You lied to me. Lied to me, Ollivander.

23:31.868 --> 23:32.993
[GRUNTS]

24:03.650 --> 24:05.568
RON:
Going somewhere?

24:09.239 --> 24:13.367
Nobody else is going to die. Not for me.

24:13.535 --> 24:15.327
For you?

24:15.495 --> 24:17.705
You think Mad-Eye died for you?

24:17.872 --> 24:20.833
You think George took that curse
for you?

24:21.585 --> 24:25.546
You may be the Chosen One, mate,
but this is a whole lot bigger than that.

24:25.714 --> 24:28.215
It's always been bigger than that.

24:30.427 --> 24:32.928
-Come with me.
-What, and leave Hermione?

24:33.388 --> 24:37.641
You mad?
We wouldn't last two days without her.

24:39.060 --> 24:40.561
Don't tell her I said that.

24:42.147 --> 24:45.357
Besides, you've still got
the Trace on you.

24:45.525 --> 24:49.612
-We've still got the wedding--
-l don't care about a wedding.

24:49.779 --> 24:54.658
I'm sorry. No matter whose it is.
I have to start finding these Horcruxes.

24:54.826 --> 24:56.785
They're our only chance to beat him...

24:56.953 --> 24:59.913
...and the longer we stay here,
the stronger he gets.

25:01.374 --> 25:03.459
Tonight's not the night, mate.

25:03.752 --> 25:06.253
We'd only be doing him a favor.

25:15.847 --> 25:16.889
[HARRY SIGHS]

25:17.057 --> 25:18.724
[BAG THUDS]

25:33.990 --> 25:35.949
Do you think he knows?

25:36.660 --> 25:42.539
I mean, they're bits of his soul,
these Horcruxes. Bits of him.

25:43.291 --> 25:47.544
When Dumbledore destroyed the ring,
you destroyed Tom Riddle's diary...

25:49.047 --> 25:51.632
...he must have felt something.

25:52.425 --> 25:56.136
To kill the other Horcruxes,
we have to find them.

25:56.513 --> 25:58.472
Where are they?

25:59.015 --> 26:01.100
Where do we start?

26:04.521 --> 26:05.646
FRED:
Ready when you are.

26:05.814 --> 26:07.189
[RON & FRED GRUNTING]

26:07.357 --> 26:11.652
ARTHUR: Please pay attention!
It's your brother's wedding. Buck up.

26:37.095 --> 26:39.179
GINNY:
Zip me up, will you?

26:53.027 --> 26:54.945
It seems silly, doesn't it, a wedding?

26:55.447 --> 26:57.823
Given everything that's going on.

26:59.159 --> 27:01.160
Maybe that's the best reason to have it...

27:01.828 --> 27:04.371
...because of everything that's going on.

27:20.388 --> 27:22.556
GEORGE:
Morning.

27:32.734 --> 27:34.902
ARTHUR:
Come on, keep up.

27:35.653 --> 27:37.237
All together now.

27:37.405 --> 27:42.868
One, two, three.

27:52.921 --> 27:55.380
How's it looking at your end, boys?

27:56.007 --> 27:57.925
FRED & GEORGE:
Brilliant.

28:00.053 --> 28:04.890
Bloody hell.
What's the Minister of Magic doing here?

28:10.772 --> 28:12.648
To what do we owe the pleasure,
Minister?

28:12.815 --> 28:17.402
I think we both know the answer
to that question, Mr. Potter.

28:25.078 --> 28:26.954
And this is...?

28:35.004 --> 28:38.924
SCRlMGEOUR: "Herein is set forth
the last will and testament...

28:39.092 --> 28:43.679
...of Albus Percival Wulfric
Brian Dumbledore.

28:43.846 --> 28:47.307
First, to Ronald Bilius Weasley...

28:48.476 --> 28:51.812
...l leave my Deluminator...

28:51.980 --> 28:54.231
...a device of my own making...

28:54.399 --> 28:59.653
...in the hope that,
when things seem most dark...

29:01.281 --> 29:04.157
...it will show him the light."

29:10.039 --> 29:13.166
-Dumbledore left this for me?
-Yeah.

29:14.085 --> 29:15.669
Brilliant.

29:16.713 --> 29:18.547
What is it?

29:30.685 --> 29:32.311
Wicked.

29:35.565 --> 29:37.566
"To Hermione Jean Granger...

29:37.734 --> 29:42.904
...l leave my copy of
The Tales of Beedle the Bard...

29:43.072 --> 29:47.743
...in the hope that she find it
entertaining and instructive."

29:48.536 --> 29:49.870
RON:
Mom used to read me those.

29:50.747 --> 29:52.289
"The Wizard and the Hopping Pot."

29:52.457 --> 29:55.375
"Babbitty Rabbitty
and the Cackling Stump."

29:57.170 --> 30:00.547
Come on, Babbitty Rabbitty.

30:01.007 --> 30:02.716
No?

30:03.051 --> 30:05.844
"To Harry James Potter...

30:06.387 --> 30:10.098
...l leave the Snitch he caught
in his first Quidditch match at Hogwarts...

30:10.266 --> 30:15.312
...as a reminder
of the rewards of perseverance...

30:17.565 --> 30:19.733
...and skill."

30:39.796 --> 30:42.881
-ls that it, then?
-Not quite.

30:43.049 --> 30:48.428
Dumbledore left you a second bequest:

30:48.680 --> 30:51.682
The sword of Godric Gryffindor.

30:53.267 --> 30:57.896
Unfortunately, the sword of Gryffindor
was not Dumbledore's to give away.

30:58.272 --> 31:01.024
As an important historical artifact,
it belongs--

31:01.192 --> 31:02.275
HERMlONE:
To Harry.

31:03.111 --> 31:05.070
It belongs to Harry.

31:05.238 --> 31:07.948
It came to him when he needed it
in the Chamber of Secrets.

31:08.116 --> 31:10.992
The sword may present itself
to any worthy Gryffindor.

31:11.160 --> 31:13.495
That does not make it
that wizard's property.

31:14.956 --> 31:18.583
And, in any event, the current
whereabouts of the sword are unknown.

31:18.751 --> 31:21.336
HARRY: Excuse me?
-The sword is missing.

31:22.714 --> 31:26.258
I don't know what you're up to,
Mr. Potter...

31:26.426 --> 31:30.387
...but you can't fight this war
on your own.

31:30.555 --> 31:32.973
He's too strong.

31:39.021 --> 31:41.022
[FOLK MUSlC PLAYlNG]

32:34.160 --> 32:35.410
LUNA:
Hello, Harry.

32:36.329 --> 32:40.332
I've interrupted a deep thought, haven't I?
I can see it growing smaller in your eyes.

32:40.500 --> 32:42.042
Of course not. How are you, Luna?

32:42.210 --> 32:44.836
Very well. Got bitten by a garden gnome
only moments ago.

32:45.004 --> 32:47.339
Gnome saliva is very beneficial.

32:47.507 --> 32:49.883
Xenophilius Lovegood.
We live just over the hill.

32:50.051 --> 32:51.218
Pleasure to meet you, sir.

32:51.385 --> 32:54.179
I trust you know, Mr. Potter,
that we at The Quibbler...

32:54.347 --> 32:56.681
...unlike those toadies
at The Daily Prophet...

32:56.849 --> 32:59.434
...fully supported Dumbledore
in his lifetime...

32:59.602 --> 33:03.271
...and, in his death,
support you just as fully.

33:03.564 --> 33:04.940
Thank you.

33:05.107 --> 33:07.943
Come, Daddy.
Harry doesn't want to talk to us right now.

33:08.110 --> 33:10.403
He's just too polite to say so.

33:10.571 --> 33:12.656
XENOPHILIUS:
Harry Potter.

33:16.202 --> 33:18.328
Excuse me, sir? May l sit down?

33:18.496 --> 33:21.915
Mr. Potter. By all means. Here.

33:22.083 --> 33:23.750
HARRY:
Thanks.

33:26.420 --> 33:29.756
I found what you wrote
in The Daily Prophet really moving.

33:30.299 --> 33:33.093
You obviously knew Dumbledore well.

33:33.261 --> 33:36.221
Well, l certainly knew him the longest.

33:36.389 --> 33:39.099
That is, if you don't count his brother,
Aberforth...

33:39.267 --> 33:42.310
...and somehow, people never do
seem to count Aberforth.

33:42.645 --> 33:44.729
-l didn't even know he had a brother.
-Ah.

33:44.897 --> 33:48.441
Well, Dumbledore was always
very private, even as a boy.

33:48.609 --> 33:50.026
Don't despair, Elphias.

33:50.194 --> 33:54.614
I'm told he's been thoroughly
unriddled by Rita Skeeter...

33:54.782 --> 33:57.617
...in 800 pages, no less.

33:58.286 --> 34:02.664
Word has it that someone talked to her.

34:02.832 --> 34:05.625
Someone who knew
the Dumbledore family well.

34:06.043 --> 34:09.629
Both you and l know who that is,
Elphias.

34:09.797 --> 34:11.298
A monstrous betrayal.

34:13.175 --> 34:14.801
Who are we talking about?

34:16.262 --> 34:18.388
Bathilda Bagshot.

34:20.057 --> 34:21.141
-Who?
MURlEL: My God, boy...

34:21.309 --> 34:26.062
...she's only the most celebrated
magical historian of the last century.

34:27.773 --> 34:31.985
She was as close
to the Dumbledores as anyone.

34:32.153 --> 34:37.198
Oh, l'm sure Rita Skeeter thought
it well worth a trip to Godric's Hollow...

34:37.366 --> 34:40.577
...to take a peek
into that old bird's rattled cage.

34:40.745 --> 34:42.579
Godric's Hollow?

34:42.997 --> 34:44.915
Bathilda Bagshot
lives at Godric's Hollow?

34:45.333 --> 34:47.417
Well, that's where
she first met Dumbledore.

34:47.585 --> 34:49.461
You don't mean to say
he lived there too?

34:49.629 --> 34:53.173
The family moved there
after his father killed those three Muggles.

34:53.341 --> 34:57.010
Oh, it was quite the scandal.

34:57.178 --> 35:02.015
Honestly, my boy,
are you sure you knew him at all?

35:20.785 --> 35:22.786
[GASPlNG AND MURMURING]

35:28.459 --> 35:31.544
SHACKLEBOLT:
The Ministry has fallen.

35:32.213 --> 35:36.091
The Minister of Magic is dead.

35:38.552 --> 35:40.887
[WHlSPERlNG]
They are coming.

35:41.055 --> 35:45.892
They are coming.

35:46.060 --> 35:47.560
WOMAN 1 :
They're coming!

35:49.563 --> 35:51.398
Nice meeting you, Mr. Potter.

35:51.983 --> 35:53.566
[WOMAN 2 SHRIEKS]

36:02.493 --> 36:04.869
HARRY: Ginny!
-Harry! Go!

36:05.037 --> 36:06.079
Go!

36:08.249 --> 36:10.458
[HORN HONKS]

36:19.427 --> 36:22.011
Here you go, sightseeing tour?
Leaves in 1 5 minutes.

36:23.431 --> 36:26.099
-Where are we?
-Shaftesbury Avenue.

36:26.267 --> 36:29.436
I used to come to the theater here
with Mom and Dad.

36:29.603 --> 36:31.855
I don't know why I thought of it.
It just popped into my head.

36:33.274 --> 36:35.108
This way.

36:38.904 --> 36:40.989
HERMlONE:
We need to change.

36:46.954 --> 36:48.204
RON:
How the ruddy...?

36:48.372 --> 36:50.957
Undetectable Extension Charm.

36:51.375 --> 36:53.626
You're amazing, you are.

36:53.836 --> 36:56.421
Always the tone of surprise.

36:56.589 --> 36:58.256
[THUD]

36:58.424 --> 37:00.550
Ah. That'll be the books.

37:06.056 --> 37:07.932
What about all the people
at the wedding?

37:08.100 --> 37:10.560
-Do you think we should go back?
-They were after you.

37:10.728 --> 37:12.896
We'd put everyone in danger
by going back.

37:13.063 --> 37:14.606
[MUFFLED MUSIC
PLAYlNG OVER HEADPHONES]

37:14.774 --> 37:16.483
-Ron's right.
WAITRESS: Ahem.

37:16.650 --> 37:18.318
Coffee?

37:18.861 --> 37:21.905
HERMlONE: A cappuccino, please.
-You?

37:22.740 --> 37:26.034
-What she said.
-Same.

37:29.413 --> 37:33.249
So where do we go from here?
Leaky Cauldron?

37:33.626 --> 37:34.709
It's too dangerous.

37:35.628 --> 37:39.172
If Voldemort has taken over the Ministry,
none of the old places are safe.

37:39.340 --> 37:42.383
Everyone from the wedding
will have gone underground, into hiding.

37:42.551 --> 37:45.053
My rucksack with all my things,
I've left it at the Burrow.

37:45.221 --> 37:47.222
[DOOR OPENS THEN CLOSES]

37:50.184 --> 37:52.101
You're joking.

37:52.436 --> 37:53.520
[SIGHS]

37:53.687 --> 37:57.690
I've had all the essentials packed
for days, just in case.

37:57.858 --> 38:00.026
RON:
By the way, these jeans, not my favorite.

38:01.195 --> 38:02.278
HARRY:
Down!

38:03.405 --> 38:04.697
Stupefy!

38:05.908 --> 38:07.575
[SINGlNG lNDISTINCTLY]

38:08.911 --> 38:10.662
DOLOHOV:
Expulso!

38:18.879 --> 38:20.380
[GRUNTS]

38:20.548 --> 38:22.382
Petrificus Totalus.

38:26.554 --> 38:27.595
Go.

38:28.055 --> 38:29.222
Leave.

38:33.894 --> 38:36.688
HARRY:
Lock the door, get the lights.

38:44.363 --> 38:45.738
[GLASS RATTLING]

38:45.906 --> 38:47.657
This one's name is Rowle.

38:48.158 --> 38:51.578
He was on the Astronomy Tower
the night Snape killed Dumbledore.

38:52.413 --> 38:56.916
This is Dolohov. I recognize him
from the wanted posters.

38:57.960 --> 39:00.128
So, what we gonna do with you, hey?

39:01.005 --> 39:03.089
Kill us if it was turned round,
wouldn't you?

39:03.257 --> 39:04.591
HARRY:
If we kill them, they'll know we were here.

39:04.758 --> 39:06.175
HERMlONE:
Ron.

39:06.343 --> 39:10.305
Suppose he did Mad-Eye.
How would you feel then?

39:12.266 --> 39:13.933
It's better we wipe their memories.

39:14.768 --> 39:16.769
You're the boss.

39:17.062 --> 39:18.813
Hermione...

39:21.275 --> 39:23.776
...you're the best at spells.

39:41.420 --> 39:43.630
Obliviate.

39:55.976 --> 39:57.560
HARRY:
How is it they knew we were there?

39:57.728 --> 39:59.312
HERMlONE:
Maybe you still have the Trace on you?

39:59.480 --> 40:02.941
Can't be. Trace breaks at 1 7.
It's wizarding law.

40:03.525 --> 40:04.567
[HERMlONE GASPS]

40:04.735 --> 40:06.319
What?

40:07.112 --> 40:10.073
We didn't celebrate your birthday, Harry.

40:10.449 --> 40:13.701
Ginny and l, we prepared a cake.

40:13.869 --> 40:16.829
We were going to bring it out
at the end of the wedding.

40:16.997 --> 40:20.458
I appreciate the thought, but given the fact
that we were almost killed...

40:20.626 --> 40:23.002
...by a couple of Death Eaters
a few minutes ago....

40:24.672 --> 40:26.381
Right.

40:27.174 --> 40:28.216
Perspective.

40:28.384 --> 40:31.386
We need to get off the streets,
get somewhere safe.

40:58.288 --> 40:59.539
[HERMlONE SHRIEKS]

41:04.503 --> 41:06.546
What was that all about?

41:07.506 --> 41:13.344
Probably Mad-Eye's idea,
in case Snape decided to come snooping.

41:15.139 --> 41:16.806
[CLATTERlNG]

41:21.520 --> 41:23.479
Homenum Revelio.

41:30.112 --> 41:31.946
We're alone.

41:38.746 --> 41:40.997
OLLIVANDER:
I believed another wand--

41:41.165 --> 41:43.624
VOLDEMORT: You lied to me.
OLLIVANDER: It makes no sense.

41:44.543 --> 41:46.294
[OLLIVANDER GRUNTlNG]

41:46.462 --> 41:49.422
I believed a different wand would work,
I swear.

41:50.924 --> 41:53.009
There must be another way.

42:08.567 --> 42:09.650
[CLATTERlNG]

43:01.995 --> 43:03.162
[DOOR OPENS]

43:03.330 --> 43:07.083
RON:
Harry? Hermione, where are you?

43:07.334 --> 43:09.669
I think I've found something.

43:15.968 --> 43:17.009
Lovely.

43:22.724 --> 43:26.227
"Regulus Arcturus Black."

43:26.395 --> 43:28.104
R.A.B.

43:31.692 --> 43:35.027
HARRY: "l know l will be dead
long before you read this.

43:35.195 --> 43:39.198
I have stolen the real Horcrux
and intend to destroy it."

43:39.575 --> 43:41.993
R.A.B. is Sirius's brother.

43:42.411 --> 43:44.203
Yes.

43:46.290 --> 43:50.167
Question is,
did he actually destroy the real Horcrux?

43:50.460 --> 43:52.545
[CLATTERlNG]

44:09.313 --> 44:11.480
[KREACHER GRUNTING]

44:11.899 --> 44:14.066
You've been spying on us, have you?

44:14.234 --> 44:18.696
KREACHER:
Kreacher has been watching.

44:18.864 --> 44:20.781
HERMlONE:
Maybe he knows where the real locket is.

44:23.785 --> 44:25.745
HARRY:
Have you ever seen this before?

44:25.913 --> 44:27.496
Kreacher?

44:28.332 --> 44:30.750
It's Master Regulus' locket.

44:30.918 --> 44:33.628
HARRY:
But there were two, weren't there?

44:34.630 --> 44:36.339
Where's the other one?

44:36.632 --> 44:38.633
[KREACHER WHIMPERS]

44:38.842 --> 44:43.429
Kreacher doesn't know
where the other locket is.

44:43.597 --> 44:45.973
Yes, but did you ever see it?
Was it in this house?

44:46.141 --> 44:47.308
Filthy Mudblood.

44:47.476 --> 44:49.185
-Death Eaters are coming--
-Ron.

44:49.353 --> 44:52.188
KREACHER: Blood traitor, Weasley.
-Answer her.

44:53.941 --> 44:56.192
Yes.

44:57.235 --> 45:00.696
It was here in this house.

45:01.949 --> 45:04.283
A most evil object.

45:04.451 --> 45:05.701
How do you mean?

45:06.453 --> 45:10.790
Before Master Regulus died,
he ordered Kreacher to destroy it...

45:10.958 --> 45:16.212
...but no matter how hard Kreacher tried,
he could not do it.

45:16.380 --> 45:17.964
Well, where is it now?

45:18.632 --> 45:23.219
-Did someone take it?
-He came in the night.

45:23.387 --> 45:28.057
He took many things,
including the locket.

45:28.225 --> 45:29.767
Who did?

45:30.435 --> 45:32.019
Who was it, Kreacher?

45:34.564 --> 45:37.233
Mundungus.

45:37.401 --> 45:40.903
Mundungus Fletcher.

45:41.989 --> 45:43.572
Find him.

46:02.551 --> 46:04.218
[DOOR OPENS]

46:05.095 --> 46:06.554
My father will hear about this.

46:11.852 --> 46:13.728
NEVILLE:
Hey, losers.

46:14.479 --> 46:16.689
He isn't here.

46:30.370 --> 46:32.747
As your new Minister for Magic...

46:32.956 --> 46:38.127
...l promise to restore
this temple of tolerance...

46:38.295 --> 46:39.962
...to its former glory.

46:41.381 --> 46:43.215
Therefore, beginning today...

46:44.259 --> 46:48.054
...each employee
will submit themselves...

46:48.722 --> 46:50.931
...for evaluation.

46:51.808 --> 46:54.810
But know this:
You have nothing to fear...

46:56.229 --> 46:57.980
...if you have nothing to hide.

46:58.398 --> 47:00.024
[CHUCKLES]

47:02.402 --> 47:03.986
-How much?
-Two Galleons.

47:04.154 --> 47:06.655
Come on, time is money. Cheers, pal.

47:06.823 --> 47:08.741
MAN 1 : Snatchers!
MAN 2: Move out of the way.

47:14.956 --> 47:16.415
-l told you.
MAN 3: Get out.

47:16.583 --> 47:17.625
MAN 2:
Squash him.

47:22.464 --> 47:23.923
[THUNDER RUMBLES]

47:24.341 --> 47:26.675
[RON PLAYING BEETHOVEN'S
"FÜR ELISE" OFF-KEY]

47:26.843 --> 47:28.469
Be a bit gentler.

47:32.307 --> 47:34.308
[HERMlONE PLAYING
BEETHOVEN'S "FÜR ELlSE"]

47:39.856 --> 47:42.191
[RON CONTINUES
PLAYlNG OFF-KEY]

47:49.991 --> 47:52.660
[WHlRRING]

47:54.579 --> 47:56.705
They have flesh memories.

47:58.834 --> 48:04.380
When Scrimgeour first gave it to you,
I thought it might open at your touch.

48:05.215 --> 48:07.967
That Dumbledore had hidden
something inside it.

48:08.218 --> 48:09.885
MAN [ON RADlO]:
Many of you are wondering...

48:10.053 --> 48:12.972
...why Voldemort has yet to show himself
now that he has vanquished...

48:13.139 --> 48:16.225
...the most powerful symbol of opposition
to him and his followers.

48:18.270 --> 48:19.311
MUNDUNGUS [MUFFLED]:
Get off.

48:19.479 --> 48:22.231
Harry Potter, so long it's been.

48:22.691 --> 48:24.024
MUNDUNGUS [IN NORMAL VOlCE]:
Get off me.

48:24.484 --> 48:26.819
[ALL GRUNTING]

48:29.656 --> 48:33.576
As requested,
Kreacher has returned with the thief...

48:33.743 --> 48:35.744
-Expelliarmus.
-...Mundungus Fletcher.

48:35.912 --> 48:39.123
What you playing at? Setting a pair
of bleeding house-elves after me.

48:39.291 --> 48:40.791
Dobby was only trying to help.

48:40.959 --> 48:45.337
Dobby saw Kreacher in Diagon Alley,
which Dobby thought was curious.

48:45.505 --> 48:49.842
And then Dobby heard Kreacher
mention Harry Potter's name.

48:50.010 --> 48:52.845
-l just--
-And then Dobby saw Kreacher...

48:53.013 --> 48:55.806
-...talking with the thief, Mundungus--
-l'm no thief.

48:55.974 --> 48:58.893
You foul little-- Git.

48:59.311 --> 49:03.689
I'm a purveyor
of rare and wondrous objects.

49:03.857 --> 49:05.733
You're a thief, Dung. Everyone knows it.

49:05.901 --> 49:08.861
Master Weasley,
so good to see you again.

49:09.029 --> 49:10.070
Wicked trainers.

49:10.238 --> 49:11.655
[NEWSPAPERS THUD]

49:11.823 --> 49:14.575
Listen, l panicked that night, all right?

49:16.202 --> 49:18.454
Could l help it
if Mad-Eye fell off his broom?

49:20.457 --> 49:21.874
KREACHER: You....
HERMlONE: Tell the truth.

49:22.042 --> 49:24.835
When you turned this place over--
Don't deny it.

49:25.003 --> 49:26.545
--you found a locket, am I right?

49:26.713 --> 49:28.964
Why? Was it valuable?

49:29.132 --> 49:30.257
HERMlONE:
You still got it?

49:30.425 --> 49:32.885
No, he's worried
he didn't get enough money for it.

49:33.053 --> 49:34.553
Bleeding give it away, didn't l?

49:34.721 --> 49:35.763
[SIGHS]

49:35.931 --> 49:39.058
There l was,
flogging me wares in Diagon Alley...

49:39.225 --> 49:43.228
...when some Ministry hag comes up
and asks to see me license.

49:43.438 --> 49:45.522
Says she's a mind to lock me up.

49:45.690 --> 49:49.360
And would've done it too,
if she hadn't taken a fancy to that locket.

49:49.527 --> 49:53.447
-Who was she? The witch. Do you know?
-No, I--

49:58.244 --> 50:01.664
Well, she's there. Look.

50:03.792 --> 50:06.168
Bleeding bow and all.

50:31.111 --> 50:32.111
[GRUNTS]

50:42.205 --> 50:44.206
[SNORING]

50:47.002 --> 50:50.796
Right, remember what we said.

50:51.047 --> 50:54.800
Don't speak to anyone
unless absolutely necessary.

50:55.051 --> 50:59.972
Just try and act normal.
Do what everybody else is doing.

51:00.390 --> 51:03.517
If we do that, then with a bit of luck,
we'll get inside.

51:03.685 --> 51:05.310
-And then--
-lt gets really tricky.

51:05.478 --> 51:07.312
-Correct.
-Yeah.

51:07.480 --> 51:10.399
-This is completely mental.
-Completely.

51:10.567 --> 51:12.609
The world's mental.

51:12.777 --> 51:14.194
Come on...

51:14.821 --> 51:17.239
...we've got a Horcrux to find.

51:43.099 --> 51:45.100
[TOlLETS FLUSHING]

52:11.127 --> 52:13.545
RON:
We flush ourselves in.

52:17.550 --> 52:20.344
That's bloody disgusting.

52:27.143 --> 52:29.144
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

52:48.373 --> 52:50.040
GUARD 1 :
Name?

52:51.334 --> 52:52.876
GUARD 2:
You. Come.

52:53.044 --> 52:55.212
MAN: What? What?
GUARD 2: Come on.

52:55.380 --> 52:57.798
-What did l do?
-Just keep walking.

53:05.181 --> 53:07.099
HARRY: Are those--?
HERMlONE: Muggles.

53:07.267 --> 53:11.895
In their rightful place.

53:13.648 --> 53:16.859
Gotta tell you,
I'm starting to freak out a bit.

53:19.112 --> 53:23.615
How long did you say this batch
of Polyjuice would last, Hermione?

53:24.158 --> 53:25.200
I didn't.

53:25.368 --> 53:26.410
[ELEVATOR DINGS]

53:32.375 --> 53:34.293
YAXLEY:
Cattermole.

53:35.336 --> 53:38.964
